phase2.explanation:
You're trying to use a SpriteRenderer that either isn't assigned or the GameObject doesn't have one.

**The fix:**
```csharp
void Start()
{
    SpriteRenderer sr = GetComponent<SpriteRenderer>();
    if (sr != null)
    {
        sr.color = Color.red;
    }
    else
    {
        Debug.LogError("No SpriteRenderer found!");
    }
}
```

**Sharp-chan says:**
"Always check if a component exists before using it. It's the safe way."
